'''Our Lady of Lourdes Hospital''' is a 197 bed<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.lourdes.com/about-us/media-center/fact-sheets/general-fact-sheet/|title = Lourdes Fact Sheet|last =|first =|date =|website =|publisher =|access-date =}}</ref> [[community hospital]] in [[Binghamton, New York]], [[United States]].
In 1983, the hospital was selected by the [[Federal government of the United States|US Federal Government]] to take part in a national [[cancer]] research project.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/08/02/us/cancer-therapy-will-expand-in-communities-across-us.html|title=Cancer therapy will expand in communities across U.S.|date=August 2, 1983|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=13 June 2011|location=[[Washington, D.C.]]}}</ref> In 2006, a flood cost the hospital several million dollars in damages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbs6albany.com/news/hospital-11925-neil-binghamton.html|title=Flood damage at Binghamton hospital could top $20 million|last=Joseph|first=Bob|date=July 9, 2006|publisher=[[CBS]]|accessdate=13 June 2011|location=[[Binghamton, New York]]}}</ref>
In 2016, the U.S. Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services released the first round of the Overall Hospital Quality Star Rating. Our Lady of Lourdes received the lowest ranking, one star.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pressconnects.com/story/news/local/new-york/2016/07/27/feds-release-new-hospital-ratings/87621894/|title=Feds release new hospital ratings|access-date=2016-08-10}}</ref> That same year, Loudes Hospital became a certified member of the [[University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center|MD Anderson Cancer Network]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wbng.com/news/local/New-cancer-treatment-center-in-Soutern-Tier-392798991.html|title=Lourdes Hospital becomes member of certified cancer network|access-date=2016-09-09}}</ref>
In 2017, Lourdes was granted a three-year/full accreditation designation by the National Accreditation Program for Breast Centers (NAPBC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lourdes.com/news/2017/05/napbc-accredited/|title=Lourdes Hospital - Lourdes Breast Care Center Accredited by National Program - Binghamton, NY|website=www.lourdes.com|language=en|access-date=2017-06-12}}</ref>
In 2018, Lourdes was ranked as the 21st best hospital in New York according to the U.S. News Best Hospitals specialty rankings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.usnews.com/best-hospitals/area/ny|title=US News|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
