{{Infobox television| |show_name = Tourettes: I Swear I Can't Help It |image = |caption = |runtime = 66 minutes |director = Phillipa Robinson |producer = Phillipa Robinson |country = United Kingdom |presenter = [[Eleanor Bron]] (narrator) |channel = [[BBC One|BBC1]] |first_aired = 28 May 2009 |website = }} '''''Tourettes: I Swear I Can't Help It''''' is a ''[[Q.E.D. (BBC TV series)|QED]]'' documentary made by the [[BBC]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00ksj56 |title=BBC One - Tourettes: I Swear I Can't Help It |publisher=BBC |date=28 May 2009 |accessdate=13 June 2012}}</ref>
==Overview== The film follows John Davidson, who has [[Tourette syndrome]] (TS), and the changes in his life since the 1989 QED [[documentary]] ''[[John's Not Mad]]''. Another individual with TS, Greg, was filmed by his mother; his [[tic]]s occasionally make him collapse or appear frozen. In this film, the pair meet and see how each copes with the condition.
